Perf review season is here! I was collecting some helpful resources for Prateek, and I thought I should share them here also for easy reference:

• Here is our engineering levels doc (https://docs.google.com/document/d/1vC7lSud2WXHGNZZSr3h1tY6ddfWraQfNRYj9mMFp6Zg/edit)
• Feedback best practices (https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Gjeziz-1C7iU6QQYUYLHYUtS9tYeNw9w4Q8p4IS3mcU/edit?tab=t.0#heading=h.wjhqlnp3r85b)
• These slides (https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/13SxQlmRAB4I8qsYMX_5vjhV825T4kiQCItXa3Ngu9rA/edit#slide=id.gf53e7712ec_0_795) can be a helpful resource if you want to learn more about calibration
There are more helpful resources in the email that HR sent out yesterday!
